  "response": "Here are some ways to relax at work:\n\n1. Physical techniques\n- Take deep, slow breaths\n- Practice brief stretching\n- Use progressive muscle relaxation\n- Do subtle desk exercises\n\n2. Mental strategies\n- Use short meditation breaks\n- Listen to calming music with headphones\n- Practice mindfulness\n- Take short mental breaks\n\n3. Workspace adjustments\n- Organize your workspace\n- Add a plant or personal photo\n- Use ergonomic equipment\n- Adjust lighting\n\n4. Time management\n- Break tasks into smaller steps\n- Take regular short breaks\n- Prioritize tasks\n- Set realistic goals\n\n5. Stress reduction\n- Avoid caffeine overload\n- Stay hydrated\n- Eat healthy snacks\n- Maintain good sleep habits\n\n6. Boundary setting\n- Learn to say no\n- Communicate effectively\n- Don't overcommit\n- Set clear work-life boundaries\n\n7. Quick relaxation techniques\n- 5-minute walking break\n- Brief guided breathing exercises\n- Hand or neck massage\n- Positive visualization\n\n8. Social support\n- Talk to supportive colleagues\n- Share concerns with supervisor\n- Seek workplace wellness resources\n\nRemember, different techniques work for different people, so experiment to find what helps you most.",
